MAKKAH: Sheik Abdulah Kromah, chairman of the Hajj and Umrah Committee in Liberia, has commended the facilities and services offered by Saudi Arabia to Hajj and Umrah pilgrims. Following a recent meeting with the Chairman of the Mutawwifin Company for pilgrims of non-Arab African countries, Ahmad Sindi, Kromah said the mega projects at the two Holy Mosques and other holy sites represent clear evidence for the attention paid by the Saudi government to care for pilgrims, which highlight the governmentâ€™s keenness to offer more services every year to ensure that pilgrims and Umrah performers complete their rituals with ease. The official also praised the services provided by Hajj companies.  